Rottm Abraham de bra
t sedert mijnen laesten van 29 pas geene van ue ondestusschen
dencke mijn pack N 27 al is versonden, hebbe advis van londen
als dat vieder het geleyt van de transport schepen naer cosby soude
comen Clacs Jacobs aen wieur boort voor my is gelaeden een
pack N38, & alsoo in d amsterdamsche gaset vermelt dat het
selve convoy inde maeke binnen was soo verhope den voorschr
claes iacobsen daer by sal wesen derhalven ingesloten het cognossemen
& sult gelieven te verclaeren voor 12 coleure gemengelde lakens
risaerden

12 be
3 mey
Lnden M Wall & Will Kent
2y ob sence my last to you on the 29 past recd yours of 13 d with
acctt & patt of N36 aboard Claes Jacob for Rott, where
the transport ships are arrived from londen, so hope said Jacobs
be by them the mode cullours are to much upon the red, they should
be upon chestmit cullour, I could have wished some to the patt 4 & 5
of my order of 15 march had been ty which please to provide as
also what whantes to my orders sence given as also 29 past the
convoij from amst is sailed to hull so gett the baeyes & northrens
fom them reddy whilst I rest
Cortryck de wed Caure

Londen wall & Will Kent
sence my last of 3 curt non from you, butt haveinge undersbrod
that som the packett boat which carried our lettres of 26 past is baken
fran the fronch, so have you hibove copie, of what I then writt
Reuve
you, al also the seconds bills of which I then sent you the first: viz
£2410:- in 2 bills on sJoseph Herne & £200 on John loyd for which
procure the needfull & advise mee, nterim I hope, you have readdy by
this time what s pa clothes I have ordered, wh which send mee the patt
as soon as readdy to direct my orders accordingley for more, please not to
ship them butt when the convoy present for to depart either
for holland or ostend, butt I had rather that for ostend was firsnd
in exspectution to know what further passes I rest
AMmst Rover
